37:25.614 --> 37:31.142
the same, I guess. 96 pounds on a 155 and a lesser 
amount on a 105. But 32 battalions, 32 times 12

37:38.218 --> 37:45.408
times 18 in some instances. This would give you 32 
times 12 is a good balance. That number of guns were

37:49.774 --> 37:55.603
the rounds all hitting and exploding at the same 
time. A little sergeant did that. Brought all that

37:58.847 --> 38:00.690
artillery in. Artillery in World War II was the 
best arm that we had in our army. In Vietnam, it was

38:08.232 --> 38:10.315
the lousiest. That's how we progressed with our 
artillery. All rounds hit on those 22 tanks at the

38:15.924 --> 38:21.052
same time. No kidding? Every round burst at the 
same time. This was so devastating.

38:32.041 --> 38:41.512
to those tanks that they left three dead ones and 
