39:52.265 --> 39:59.136
other two regiments that attacked us withdrew, 
and they were using this as their last gas, and they

39:52.265 --> 39:59.136
withdrew. Why did they withdraw? Because of the 
artillery? No, because of our tank action. We

40:04.484 --> 40:07.088
killed a lot of their tanks. I see. Because you 
could deal with it lighter. Yeah, they're

40:10.313 --> 40:11.435
lighter. They're Mark Fours and Mark Fives,

40:11.475 --> 40:19.487
yes. It's

40:21.796 --> 40:30.893
getting dark, and we're consolidating our 
losses, getting casualties back. We're

40:30.933 --> 40:37.966
refueling, re-ammoing, trying to get our stuff 
together, and still keeping the artillery on

40:30.933 --> 40:37.966
them. And next morning again, we jump off during 
the night. The assessment's made.

40:46.180 --> 40:55.112
Hollingsworth, Task Force Hollingsworth, you go 
take Gernsweiler, their regimental objective,

40:46.180 --> 40:55.112
or the combat command B objective. So I did. How 
